# Public Repositories for Erlware Development

## Official Repositories

These are the repositories with the [official Erlware code][erlware]; their
master's head compose the head of Erlware's development.

[Erlware site][site] builds regularly from `erlware-site` head every four hours.

## Public Repositories from Contributors

 * **Dave Peticolas:** [http://git.krondo.com/erlware/][dave]

# Public Developing Pages

## Official Google Code Pages

We use Google Code to host downloads and issues for the next sub-projects:

  * [Reverl][reverl] proxy, load balancer and HTTPS front-end for Web server(s).
  * [Ktuo][ktuo] - This library implements a library for parsing and encoding
    JSON and tuple objects.
  * [Fconf][fconf] - A highly flexible general configuration system for Erlang
    applications.
  * [Tercio][tercio] - Erlang centric web application system.


